# Stripe Development Context

When building or modifying Stripe integrations, use these LLM-friendly resources.

## Plain text docs

Access Stripe docs as plain text markdown by appending `.md` to any URL:

- [https://docs.stripe.com/building-with-llms.md](https://docs.stripe.com/building-with-llms.md)
- Any doc page: `https://docs.stripe.com/<path>.md`

Benefits: fewer tokens, full content (including hidden tabs), better LLM parsing.

## LLMs.txt

- [https://docs.stripe.com/llms.txt.md](https://docs.stripe.com/llms.txt.md) — instructions for AI tools on retrieving plain text docs.
- [llmstxt.org](https://llmstxt.org/) — emerging standard for LLM-accessible content.

## Stripe MCP (Model Context Protocol)

The Stripe MCP provides tools for AI agents to:

- Interact with the Stripe API
- Search Stripe docs and support

[Connect your agent](https://docs.stripe.com/mcp.md) to the Stripe MCP server.

## Stripe VS Code extension

- AI Assistant for Stripe API questions and code suggestions
- [Stripe for VS Code](https://docs.stripe.com/stripe-vscode.md)
- Use `@stripe` in Copilot chat for Stripe-specific assistance

## Stripe Agent Toolkit SDK

For agentic software:

- Create Stripe objects
- Charge for agent usage
- Compatible with OpenAI Agent SDK, Vercel AI SDK, Langchain, CrewAI

[Learn more](https://docs.stripe.com/agents.md)
